	<td bgcolor="#160022" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Also, will Provoke and other abilities be amplified by buffs and other effects?<br />
<br />
I can imagine a Warrior with a Furious Bash V shield from BoT and buffed with the Shadow Knight Voice of Thule buff doing a Provoke that generates (400 * 1.62 = ) 648 Hate; if the skill is treated as a spell effect.  Actually, I think the Voice spell line amplifies any source of aggro, so Provoke is going to at least gain this bonus, if not the Furious Bash bonus.<br />
<br />
I know I may be nit-picking min/maxing the results of these changes, but the fact of the matter is that Warriors ARE at the top of the list in terms of defensive abilities.  However marginal that lead is, or how dependent on gear, they ARE at the top.  To provide Warriors with the most superior Defensive abilities, AND make aggro so easy to maintain...is a wee bit off balance, imo.<br />
<br />
I will withhold final judgement until it is published serverwide, but honestly I think the day is comming when nuking with impunity will be the norm.<br />
<br />
*edit* Velocir, Warriors are the tank of choice on Raid encounters.  This is going to be made more true with the 5% bonus to mitigation they are receiving.  They have defensive, and a higher hit point base to expand upon than Knights.  YES, I understand that gear has everything to do with the validity of this statement, and that Knights have been successfully used to tank the highest end raid bosses...from two expansions ago (PoP).  The point is that you won't NEED to use any fancy strategies for Warriors to get burst aggro.  You won't NEED to do anything at all, just let the Warrior use his new fancy skills and all is well.  Why do I think this is imbalanced when Knights evidently already do this?  Well at least the spells a Knight uses can be interrupted, they require mana, they have a casting time, they can fizzle, and as mentioned before Knights are at an innate disadvantage in terms of defensive abilities when compared to Warriors which are about to be made MORE APPARENT with the change to the melee system and introduction of special skills.  To say that Warriors and Knights are equal in the tanking field is simply wrong.  While the top 99% of players may disagree, look at the game as a whole, and look at which class is chosen to tank the first time you engage a new boss, then say they are equal.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
