	<td bgcolor="#160022" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >youre right, theyre not equal. however, they are close enough.<br />
<br />
while a warrior will always be used to tank a new mob, they can be eventually be sidelined for a knight who will generate much more overall agro, completely devoiding warriors of their only job. <br />
<br />
on raids, knights already have the important role of tank mezzing adds and non-damage tanking. they can also be used to tank lesser hitting mobs very easily for an overall increase in raid DPS.<br />
<br />
obtaining quick agro as opposed to what warriors can do now, is really not that big of a deal. with a bow or better, debuffs can land fine in a couple seconds and nuke DPS just has to 'ease' into their DPS a little. the only thing this may do is save the life of a shammy or chanter in an extreme situation.<br />
<br />
even with these changes, knights will still hold much better overall agro as the gap is between a warriors agro line and a knights is way to wide for this to make a difference. not to mention that warriors will be giving up other abilities for the duration of it. <br />
<br />
and as for knights, spell fizzles and interupts are not going to make much of a difference once agro is established unless there is a very large lack of luck involved.<br />
<br />
<br />
overall, i cant see much of a difference in raids besides people being 2-3 seconds happier. as it is for groups, similarly equiped warriors have no appeal over knights unless youre taking on a named in a hard adventure, which is still not close to a necessity.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
