<table bgcolor="#000000" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor="#663399"  width="100%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#160022" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post227210"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>taelen</b></font><br>
	
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Forum Apprentice</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>

<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Server: Tallon Zek<br></font>




	
	<td bgcolor="#160022" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >"If you want more mitigation (less healing) go with a warrior, if you want high dps (especially burst) go for the SK/pally."<br />
<br />
Yeesh, that line is so uninformed.<br />
<br />
Having a warrior in group does mean *slightly* better mitigation.  However, it certainly does *not* mean less healing.  Why?  Aggro control.  A warrior will lose aggro to a caster much more often than a pally or sk, leading to the casters needing inefficient quick heals.  Additionally, sk's can lifetap and pallies can heal.  So a warrior means *more* healing for the cleric or whoever is the primary healer.  If the casters cut down their dps to avoid needing heals then the warrior takes *more* damage than the sk or pally because the drop in dps from the group means the mob has more time to do damage.<br />
<br />
Your second sentence.  Warriors have higher dps than sk's or pallies, even if you include spell damage from the knights.  DPS is not the issue here, and mitigation is a lesser issue.<br />
<br />
The real issue is that warriors have significantly less aggro control than pallies or sk's *and* pallies and sk's have many many other benefits that come from their spells.  What all the warriors really wanted was taunt fixed, plain and simple.  They wanted to have decent aggro control to be able to compete with knights.  All of these fancy changes SoE is introducing were not at the prompting of the warrior community, they are internal from SoE.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p></p>
	</td>
</tr>
