<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#160022" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post227393"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><b>Axxl 01</b></font><br>
	
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Forum Apprentice</font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ></font><br>
	<p>

<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Server: Bristlebane<br></font>




	
	<td bgcolor="#160022" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >The old memory is a bit fuzzy, but when exactly did Sony remove the hybrid experience penalty?  I remember the early days of my bardic life when people would pass over paladins and shadow knights because they did not want to be affected with such a hit.  The two classes were apparently balanced against a pure warrior by having these extra power but with the experience penalty.  It seemed that when Sony (or Verant, though doubtful) removed one part of the equation, there was no balance given to the pure warrior for the sudden desire for a warrior knight with extra power.  Thus the reversal of opinion for a group began and seems to be evident even today.<br />
<br />
So many years later, Sony is slowly rebalancing the scales it seems, much to the dismay of knights that fear they will suddenly be undesirable.  Knowing Sony, these changes will be either half-assed or so overboard that it will be a while before the happy medium is met.  If ever...<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Axlrose - ...&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p></p>
	</td>
